		<li><strong>Color Options:</strong> Black (most popular), bronze, white, custom colors to match home</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Tall Wood Privacy Fencing with Security Enhancements</h3>
	<p><strong>Security Through Privacy:</strong> Solid wood fencing creates complete visual barriers that prevent criminals from easily surveying your property. However, this must be balanced carefully—overly private fences can also provide concealment for criminals once they're on your property.</p>

	<p><strong>Security-Enhanced Wood Fence Features:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Height:</strong> Maximum 6 feet in rear yards per Stockton regulations (sufficient for security)</li>
		<li><strong>Board Spacing:</strong> No gaps between boards for complete privacy</li>
		<li><strong>Board Direction:</strong> Install boards on interior side—prevents use as climbing ladder</li>
		<li><strong>Top Treatment:</strong> Lattice top, pointed caps, or decorative toppers deter climbing</li>
		<li><strong>Reinforced Gates:</strong> Steel frames inside wood for strength, quality locks and hinges</li>
		<li><strong>Bottom Security:</strong> Concrete base or buried boards prevent digging/crawling under</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Best Wood Choices for Stockton Security Fencing:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Cedar:</strong> Naturally durable, resists rot and insects. Aromatic properties may deter pests. Cost: $20-40/LF installed.</li>
		<li><strong>Redwood:</strong> Premium durability, beautiful appearance, excellent Stockton climate performance. Cost: $25-45/LF installed.</li>
		<li><strong>Pressure-Treated Pine:</strong> Most affordable, good longevity with maintenance. Cost: $15-30/LF installed.</li>
		<li><strong>Composite:</strong> Zero maintenance, won't rot or split, 25+ year life. Cost: $30-60/LF installed.</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Balancing Privacy and Visibility:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Consider 4-foot solid section with 2-foot lattice top for visibility from inside home</li>
		<li>Leave front yard more open per Stockton regulations (4-foot max) for neighborhood watch effectiveness</li>
		<li>Strategic window placement allows surveillance without compromising privacy</li>
		<li>Integrate security cameras to compensate for visual barriers</li>
	</ul>

